<s-function-doc>
<s-topics>
<s-topic> plot.RCp </s-topic>
</s-topics>

<s-title>
Create an RCp Plot
</s-title>

<s-description>
Create an RCp plot.
</s-description>

<s-usage>
<s-old-style-usage>
plot.RCp(Rfile, nbest=5, J=N + 1, L=N + 1, a=3.5, CEX=1)
</s-old-style-usage>
</s-usage>

<s-args-required>
<s-arg name=" Rfile ">
an RCp object.
</s-arg>
</s-args-required>

<s-args-optional>
<s-arg name=" nbest ">
the number of 'best' selections of each size to be plotted.
</s-arg>

<s-arg name=" J ">
the upper limit of the y axis.  The default is taken to be one more than
the size of the full model.
</s-arg>

<s-arg name=" L ">
the upper limit of the x axis.  The default is taken to be the size of the
full model plus one.
</s-arg>

<s-arg name=" a ">
specifies the position of the labels of the axes.  Increasing the this
value moves the labels further away from the axis.
</s-arg>

<s-arg name=" CEX ">
character expansion parameter (cex) passed to plot (controls the size of
the characters on the plot).  The default is 1.
</s-arg>
</s-args-optional>

<s-side-effects>
a plot of RCp versus Vp is produced on a graphics device.
</s-side-effects>

<s-see>
<s-function name="RCp.sgm">RCp</s-function>,
<s-function name="par.sgm">par</s-function>.
</s-see>

<s-keywords>
<s-keyword>librobust</s-keyword>
<s-keyword>hplot</s-keyword>
</s-keywords>

<s-docclass>
function
</s-docclass>

</s-function-doc>
